      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>After reading the front-page article about hiking in the winter (''On the Trail, a Winter's Tale,'' Dec. 20), I'd like to list three essentials for cold-weather hiking, which I have unfortunately forgotten on occasion:</p>
        <p>1. Lip balm. 2. Tissues (imagine how annoying a running nose is for seven miles). 3. Earmuffs.</p>
        <p>Altough the third item might sound bulky and unnecessary, the wind picks up considerably on the top of the ridges.</p>
        <p>LUCY ANDERSON  Newark</p>
      </block>
